## Optional — Firebase (production auth & cloud sync)

When set, the app uses Firebase Auth + Firestore for login/sync. Express still needed for billing webhooks / Pro / review account.

```env
# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project
# VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project.appspot.com
# VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}
# Or: GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=path/to/serviceAccount.json
```

Deploy Firestore rules: `firebase deploy --only firestore:rules`

---

## Legacy / dev-only — Stripe (not used for iOS store billing)

Kept for old web/dev checkout paths. Mobile launch uses RevenueCat.

```env
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
# STRIPE_PRICE_ID=price_xxx
```

Apple IAP server verify (production): integrate App Store Server API; sandbox may use `APPLE_IAP_VERIFY_SKIP=true` for local testing only.
